<li id="lithub_daily_widget-9" class="widget widget_lithub_daily_widget"><div class="lithub-daily-header"><a href="/category/lit-hub-daily/"><b>Lithub</b> Daily</a></div><h2 class="widgettitle">February 27, 2025</h2>
<a href="https://lithub.com/lit-hub-daily-february-27-2025/"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-250087 size-thumbnail" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/9780330484541-us-300-e1740603542733-150x150.jpg" alt="A Heartbreaking Work of Staggering Genius" width="150" height="150" /></a>
<ul>
 	<li><a href="https://slate.com/culture/2025/02/dave-eggers-heartbreaking-work-staggering-genius-book-toph.html" class="external" target="_blank"><span style="font-weight: 400">The afterlives of </span><em><span style="font-weight: 400">A Heartbreaking Work of Staggering Genius</span></em></a></li>
 	<li><a href="https://www.nybooks.com/online/2025/02/26/patriarchal-bargains-andrea-dworkin/" class="external" target="_blank"><span style="font-weight: 400">Moira Donegan on Andrea Dworkin’s newly reissued </span><i><span style="font-weight: 400">Right-Wing Women</span></i></a></li>
 	<li><a href="https://www.nytimes.com/2025/02/26/t-magazine/blue-color-art-music-books.html" class="external" target="_blank"><span style="font-weight: 400">Literature’s obsession with blue</span></a></li>
</ul>
<a href="https://lithub.com/lit-hub-daily-february-27-2025/"><button>More News</button></a></li>
